\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces SchemaShield-Lite\xspace  pipeline. The base model receives user context and drifted tool definitions. If the emitted tool call fails validation, a repair call is issued with structured validation errors. In the primary non-oracle protocol, missing tool names are first resolved by retrying over the visible candidate tools; once a visible target tool is resolved, a repair step may be constrained to that selected tool where provider support allows.}}{4}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:pipeline}{{1}{4}{}{figure.1}{}}
